        </h2>

        <section id="Product-Functions">
            <h3> <span> 2.1</span>
                Product Functions
            </h3>
            <p>The main functionalities of this website are:
            <ul>
                <li>Create account for users</li>
                <li>Login with account created in application or with GitHub</li>
                <li> Management for account</li>
                <li> Posibility of registered users to add a camp site</li>
                <li>Users can add a review with rating and photos </li>
                <li>Users can reserve a campground</li>
                <li>Users have on his profile page a list with reserved campgrounds where they can cancel it.</li>
                <li>Every camp has informations about price, location, contanct , utilities and weather.</li>
                <li>User can see the weather of a campground for 5 days.</li>
            </ul>
            </p>
        </section>
        <section id="database">
            <h3> <span> 2.2</span>
                Database
            </h3>
            <p>
                I used MongoDB to store the information. The collections have a suggestive name: users, camps, reviews
                and books.
            </p>
        </section>
        <section id="APIs">
            <h3> <span> 2.3</span>
                APIs
            </h3>
            <p>
                To locate the campground on the map, we used an API called OpenStreeMap, and for the weather we used
                Weatherbit which gives us information for the next 5 days.
            </p>
        </section>

    </section>

